g.text: The Low Stress type is generally more relaxed. There are no significant changes or high peaks of stress level
during anytime of the day or night.
Their stress level builds up as the day goes. It goes higher and higher towards the end of the day and doesn’t
The stress level of the Early Peak type reaches the highest in the middle of the day, then it starts to drop down
in the late afternoon. Eventually they “collapse” at bed time.
The High Stress type is stressed almost all the time in day and night. Their stress level spikes up right after
waking up, and only drops down at the end of their days.
